Benefits Analysis for Proposed 316(b) Existing Facilities Rule Chapter 13: Cost and Economic Impact of Additional Option	13.3.4 Analysis Summary Table 13-10 presents a summary of compliance costs under Option 4 for publicly- and privately-owned facilities, along with government administrative costs, for each regulatory option.	For Option 4, EPA estimates total annual compliance costs for government-owned Electric Generators at $9.5 million. NPDES permitting authorities are expected to incur another $3.2 million per year to implement this option for both Electric Generators and Manufacturers, resulting in a total annual cost of approximately $12.7 million for State and local governments. The maximum compliance cost for government-owned Electric Generators in any one year under Option 4 is $17.6 million in 2033. The maximum administrative cost to NPDES authorities in any single year for administering this option is $4.0	Benefits Analysis for Proposed 316(b) Existing Facilities Rule Chapter 13: Cost and Economic Impact of Additional Option	13.4 Cost and Economic Impact Analysis – Manufacturers a.
